OL,3,CQuestions turn to Estyn in Wales'
OL,4,Creading debate
OL,6,FEarlier this year, Estyn's Chief
OL,7,FInspector and other senior staff
OL,8,Fappeared before a Senedd committee and
OL,9,Fseemed to defend cueing, an approach
OL,10,Fwhere children are encouraged to guess
OL,11,Fwords from pictures or context or
OL,12,Fmemorise whole words, despite decades
OL,13,Fof research showing it to be
OL,14,Fineffective.
OL,16,FAt one point, he appeared to confuse
OL,17,Fcueing with "cue cards" - which are
OL,18,Fnot the same thing - and said there
OL,19,Fwere "many meta-analyses" showing
OL,20,Fbenefits to using the method.
