OL,3,CQuestions turn to Estyn in Wales'
OL,4,Creading debate
OL,6,FHis stance on phonics differs
OL,7,Fconsiderably from the consensus among
OL,8,Fcognitive scientists and educational
OL,9,Fpsychologists, who say that systematic
OL,10,Fphonics - particularly synthetic
OL,11,Fapproaches that teach children to
OL,12,Fblend sounds to read - provides the
OL,13,Fstrongest evidence-based foundation
OL,14,Ffor early literacy.
OL,16,FThat consensus is supported by decades
OL,17,Fof international research and major
OL,18,Freviews in the UK, USA and Australia.
