OL,3,CQuestions turn to Estyn in Wales'
OL,4,Creading debate
OL,6,FEarlier this year, another member of
OL,7,Fthe same panel and Chair of the
OL,8,FReading Reform Foundation, Elizabeth
OL,9,FNonweiler, who supports systematic
OL,10,Fsynthetic phonics, offered to give her
OL,11,Fown presentation to provide balance.
OL,13,FMrs Nonweiler has since resigned from
OL,14,Fthe panel, saying it had "failed to
OL,15,Fproduce anything useful" and warning
OL,16,Fthat ministers were embedding "mixed
OL,17,Fmessages" into their new #8.2 million
OL,18,Fliteracy programme.
